http://www.thehindu.com/news/cities/Kochi/Consultant-to-study-business-atmosphere/article14017153.ece

The Kerala State Industrial Development Corporation (KSIDC) will rope in a consultant to study the business atmosphere in Kerala and suggest ways to improve the situation.Chairman and Managing Director of the KSIDC M. Beena said on Saturday that there was a consensus that Kerala lagged in the area among other States in the country. The consultantwill suggest ways to improve the situation, especially with regard to the legal regime regulating enterprises. She was speaking on the sidelines of a conference on Ease of Doing Business: Measures for Improvement in Kerala.In a recently released ranking by the World Bank, Kerala has been placed 18th among the States in India for its ease of doing business conditions, well behind States like Chattishgarh, Madhya Pradesh and Odisha.